article.description: — Tobias Cameron had 13 points and six rebounds as Abilene Christian won its 13th consecutive home game, rolling past Incarnate Word 85-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cameron scores 13, Abilene Christian beats Incarnate Word
article.linkText: Cameron scores 13, Abilene Christian beats Incarnate Word
article.story: ABILENE, Texas -- — Tobias Cameron had 13 points and six rebounds as Abilene Christian won its 13th consecutive home game, rolling past Incarnate Word 85-60 on Saturday. Kolton Kohl had 14 points and three blocks for Abilene Christian (21-4, 13-2 Southland Conference). Joe Pleasant added 11 points and Airion Simmons had seven rebounds. Drew Lutz had 15 points for the Cardinals (8-13, 5-9), whose losing streak reached five games. Charlie Yoder and Bradley Akhile each had 10 points. The Wildcats improve to 2-0 against the Cardinals on the season. Abilene Christian defeated Incarnate Word 75-67 on Jan. 30. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
